# Trivy CVE Suppressions for geo-api
# ===================================
# This file suppresses known-unfixable CVEs in the base image (python:3.12-slim-bookworm).
# Per D-06: each entry MUST have a comment explaining why it is ignored and when to revisit.
#
# Format:
#   # CVE-XXXX-YYYYY: [Description] in [package]
#   # Base image: python:3.12-slim-bookworm
#   # Status: No fix available in Debian bookworm as of YYYY-MM-DD
#   # Source: https://security.debian.org/tracker/CVE-XXXX-YYYYY
#   # Revisit: Check debian security tracker monthly
#   CVE-XXXX-YYYYY
#
# Entries will be populated after the first cd.yml workflow run identifies
# which HIGH/CRITICAL CVEs exist in the built image.
